# WebScrape-TUI v2.0.0 Environment Configuration Template
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual configuration values.
# The .env file will be ignored by Git to keep your sensitive data secure.

# ============================================================================
# AI Provider API Keys
# ============================================================================
# The application supports multiple AI providers for summarization, sentiment
# analysis, and advanced features. Configure at least one provider below.
# You can use multiple providers and select them at runtime.

# Google Gemini API Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
# Supports: Summarization, Sentiment Analysis, Advanced AI Features
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# OpenAI API Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Supports: Summarization, Sentiment Analysis, Advanced AI Features
# Models: GPT-4, GPT-3.5-turbo, etc.
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Anthropic Claude API Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/
# Supports: Summarization, Sentiment Analysis, Advanced AI Features
# Models: Claude 3 Opus, Sonnet, Haiku
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here

# ============================================================================
# Application Configuration (Optional)
# ============================================================================

# Log Level Configuration
# Uncomment and set to desired level: DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL
# Default: INFO
# LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# Custom Database Path
# Uncomment and modify if you want to use a different database location
# Default: scraped_data_tui_v1.0.db
# DATABASE_PATH=scraped_data_tui_v1.0.db

# Custom Log File Path
# Uncomment and modify if you want logs saved to a different location
# Default: scraper_tui_v1.0.log
# LOG_FILE_PATH=scraper_tui_v1.0.log

# Session Timeout (in hours)
# Uncomment to override default 24-hour session expiration
# Default: 24
# SESSION_TIMEOUT_HOURS=24

# ============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit .env with your actual API keys and configuration
# 3. Configure at least one AI provider (Gemini, OpenAI, or Claude)
# 4. Never commit the .env file to version control
#
# API Key Setup:
#
# Google Gemini:
#   - Visit: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
#   - Create a new API key
#   - Replace 'your_gemini_api_key_here' with your actual key
#
# OpenAI:
#   - Visit: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#   - Create a new secret key
#   - Replace 'your_openai_api_key_here' with your actual key
#
# Anthropic Claude:
#   - Visit: https://console.anthropic.com/
#   - Navigate to API Keys section
#   - Create a new API key
#   - Replace 'your_anthropic_api_key_here' with your actual key

# ============================================================================
# Security Notes
# ============================================================================
# - Keep your API keys secure and don't share them publicly
# - Use different API keys for development and production environments
# - Regenerate API keys immediately if they are accidentally exposed
# - The .env file is automatically ignored by Git (.gitignore)
# - Never commit API keys directly in code or configuration files
# - Consider using environment-specific .env files (.env.development, .env.production)
# - Monitor your API usage and set up billing alerts with your providers

